    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the tip. i'm worried about the soil p.h. tho, i heard if it's off it makes it hard for them to actually take in the nutrients even if i fertilize. how do i check that and what should i do if it's too acidic?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "pH levels are absolutely crucial, and you're right to worry about it! You can check your soil pH by getting a simple soil testing kit from a garden center, or for a more accurate reading, sending a sample to a local agricultural extension office. If your soil is too acidic, which is often the case if you've been using lots of acidic compost or if your local soil naturally leans that way, you need to raise the pH. To do this, you'll want to apply agricultural lime (calcium carbonate) to your soil. Mix it in well and wait a few weeks for it to start working its magic.",
